The paper proposes a machine learning algorithm for classification tasks, which is likely to fall under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The algorithm involves using K-nearest neighbor (KNN) graphs, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also discusses the computational cost of the algorithm, which could be relevant to the category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on synthetic and benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the category of "Data Mining" (cs.DM).
